=== INTERPRETATION ===
This smoke test captures the raw tsc behavior of all three skills before, during,
and after physically removing system-spec-kit. Actual results:

code-graph tsc (spec-kit removed): exit 2 (non-zero). The code-graph tsconfig.json
extends ../system-spec-kit/tsconfig.json, and its include list references spec-kit
and skill-advisor source files. Without spec-kit present, the extends clause and
typeRoots paths fail, producing a hard TS5083 error before any source-level check.

skill-advisor tsc (spec-kit removed): exit 2 (non-zero). The skill-advisor
tsconfig.json extends ../../system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tsconfig.json — same
TS5083 hard-fail. The symlinked embeddings directory (lib/shared/embeddings/)
would fail on import resolution if the tsconfig extended cleanly, but the extends
fail masks that signal. This is a limitation of the current tsconfig topology.

post-restore code-graph tsc: exit 2 (non-zero). Pre-existing baseline tsc errors
unrelated to this smoke test (embeddings TS6307 include-list mismatches, etc.).

post-restore skill-advisor tsc: exit 1 (non-zero). Pre-existing TS5101 baseUrl
deprecation warning on tsconfig.json line 6.

system-spec-kit restored: YES — the trap/restore mechanism worked correctly.
No permanent damage. The exit codes for both skills are identical before and
after the smoke test, confirming the test caused no regression.

Key findings for isolation-finalize:
- Both skills' tsconfigs still extend system-spec-kit, so tsc-level isolation
  verification requires a spec-kit-present environment.
- The CI isolation-check workflow (reverse-direction audits) is the production-
  grade guard. This smoke test confirms restore safety, not clean exits.
- For a future packet: in-tree tsconfigs that don't extend sibling skills would
  enable a true "delete and tsc" isolation smoke test.

Done.
